Name: Chespin
PkdxEntry: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

Name: Quilladin
PkdxEntry: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won’t start fights.

Name: Chesnaught
PkdxEntry: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

Name: Fennekin
PkdxEntry: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Braixen
PkdxEntry: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

Name: Delphox
PkdxEntry: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

Name: Froakie
PkdxEntry: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

Name: Frogadier
PkdxEntry: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

Name: Greninja
PkdxEntry: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

Name: Bunnelby
PkdxEntry: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.

Name: Diggersby
PkdxEntry: With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.

Name: Fletchling
PkdxEntry: These friendly Pokémon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.

Name: Fletchinder
PkdxEntry: From its beak, it expels embers that set the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.

Name: Talonflame
PkdxEntry: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.

Name: Scatterbug
PkdxEntry: When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.

Name: Spewpa
PkdxEntry: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.

Name: Vivillon
PkdxEntry: The patterns on this Pokémon’s wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

Name: Litleo
PkdxEntry: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.

Name: Pyroar
PkdxEntry: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride’s cubs.

Name: Pyroar
PkdxEntry: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride’s cubs.

Name: Flabébé
PkdxEntry: When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind’s embrace with an untroubled heart.

Name: Floette
PkdxEntry: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.

Name: Florges
PkdxEntry: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.

Name: Skiddo
PkdxEntry: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

Name: Gogoat
PkdxEntry: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

Name: Pancham
PkdxEntry: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.

Name: Pangoro
PkdxEntry: Although it possesses a violent temperament, it won’t put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.

Name: Furfrou
PkdxEntry: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.

Name: Espurr
PkdxEntry: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.

Name: Meowstic
PkdxEntry: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.

Name: Meowstic
PkdxEntry: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.

Name: Honedge
PkdxEntry: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.

Name: Doublade
PkdxEntry: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.

Name: Aegislash
PkdxEntry: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.

Name: Aegislash
PkdxEntry: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.

Name: Spritzee
PkdxEntry: It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.

Name: Aromatisse
PkdxEntry: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.

Name: Swirlix
PkdxEntry: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.

Name: Slurpuff
PkdxEntry: It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.

Name: Inkay
PkdxEntry: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.

Name: Malamar
PkdxEntry: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.

Name: Binacle
PkdxEntry: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.

Name: Barbaracle
PkdxEntry: Having an eye on each palm allows it to keep watch in all directions. In a pinch, its limbs start to act on their own to ensure the enemy’s defeat.

Name: Skrelp
PkdxEntry: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.

Name: Dragalge
PkdxEntry: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.

Name: Clauncher
PkdxEntry: They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.

Name: Clawitzer
PkdxEntry: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.

Name: Helioptile
PkdxEntry: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.

Name: Heliolisk
PkdxEntry: It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.

Name: Tyrunt
PkdxEntry: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn’t like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.

Name: Tyrantrum
PkdxEntry: Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.

Name: Amaura
PkdxEntry: This ancient Pokémon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.

Name: Aurorus
PkdxEntry: Using its diamond-shaped crystals, it can instantly create a wall of ice to block an opponent’s attack.

Name: Hawlucha
PkdxEntry: With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.

Name: Dedenne
PkdxEntry: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.

Name: Carbink
PkdxEntry: Born from the temperatures and pressures deep underground, it fires beams from the stone in its head.

Name: Goomy
PkdxEntry: The weakest Dragon-type Pokémon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesn’t dry out.

Name: Sliggoo
PkdxEntry: It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it can’t see anything.

Name: Goodra
PkdxEntry: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokémon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.

Name: Klefki
PkdxEntry: These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.

Name: Phantump
PkdxEntry: These Pokémon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. They prefer to live in abandoned forests.

Name: Trevenant
PkdxEntry: It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.

Name: Pumpkaboo
PkdxEntry: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

Name: Gourgeist
PkdxEntry: Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.

Name: Bergmite
PkdxEntry: It blocks opponents’ attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.

Name: Avalugg
PkdxEntry: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.

Name: Noibat
PkdxEntry: They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.

Name: Noivern
PkdxEntry: They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.

Name: Xerneas
PkdxEntry: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

Name: Yveltal
PkdxEntry: When this legendary Pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

Name: Zygarde
PkdxEntry: When the Kalos region’s ecosystem falls into disarray, it appears and reveals its secret power.

Name: Diancie
PkdxEntry: t can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.

Name: Hoopa
PkdxEntry: This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.

Name: Volcanion
PkdxEntry: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.
